00023 Function::Argument::Argument(QDomNode &argNode): name_(QString()),
00024 value_(QString()), dataType_(QString()) {
00025 
00026         // get the spirit:dataType attribute
00027         QDomNamedNodeMap attributeMap = argNode.attributes();
00028         dataType_ = attributeMap.namedItem(QString("spirit:dataType")).nodeValue();
00029 
00030         for (int i = 0; i < argNode.childNodes().count(); ++i) {
00031                 QDomNode tempNode = argNode.childNodes().at(i);
00032

00034                         name_ = tempNode.childNodes().at(0).nodeValue();
00035                 }

00200 void Function::write(QXmlStreamWriter& writer) {
00201         writer.writeStartElement("spirit:function");
00202         writer.writeAttribute("spirit:replicate", General::bool2Str(replicate_));
00203 
00204         if (!entryPoint_.isEmpty()) {
00205                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:entryPoint", entryPoint_);
00206         }
00207 
00208         // if mandatory fileRef is not defined
00209         if (fileRef_.isEmpty()) {
00210                 throw Write_error(QObject::tr("Mandatory element fileRef missing in "
00211                                 "spirit:function"));
00212         }
00213         else {
00214                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:fileRef", fileRef_);
00215         }
00216 
00217         if (!returnType_.isEmpty()) {
00218                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:returnType", returnType_);
00219         }
00220 
00221         // write each argument
00222         for (int i = 0; i < arguments_.size(); ++i) {
00223                 writer.writeStartElement("spirit:argument");
00224                 writer.writeAttribute("spirit:dataType", arguments_.at(i)->dataType_);
00225 
00226                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:name", arguments_.at(i)->name_);
00227                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:value", arguments_.at(i)->value_);
00228 
00229                 writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:argument
00230         }
00231 
00232         // start the spirit:disabled tag
00233         writer.writeStartElement("spirit:disabled");
00234 
00235         // write the attributes for the element
00236         General::writeAttributes(writer, disabledAttributes_);
00237 
00238         // write the value of the element and close the tag
00239         writer.writeCharacters(General::bool2Str(disabled_));
00240         writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:disabled
00241 
00242         for (int i = 0; i < sourceFiles_.size(); ++i) {
00243                 writer.writeStartElement("spirit:sourceFile");
00244 
00245                 writer.writeTextElement("spirit:sourceName",
00246                                 sourceFiles_.at(i)->sourceName_);
00247 
00248                 // if fileType is defined and userFileType is not defined
00249                 if (!sourceFiles_.at(i)->fileType_.isEmpty() &&
00250                                 sourceFiles_.at(i)->userFileType_.isEmpty()) {
00251                         writer.writeTextElement("spirit:fileType",
00252                                         sourceFiles_.at(i)->fileType_);
00253                 }
00254                 // if fileType is not defined and userFileType is defined
00255                 else if (sourceFiles_.at(i)->fileType_.isEmpty() &&
00256                                 !sourceFiles_.at(i)->userFileType_.isEmpty()) {
00257                         writer.writeTextElement("spirit:userFileType",
00258                                         sourceFiles_.at(i)->userFileType_);
00259                 }
00260                 // if both are defined or neither is defined
00261                 else {
00262                         throw Write_error(QObject::tr("Invalid spirit:sourceFile element "
00263                                         "within spirit:function"));
00264                 }
00265 
00266                 writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:sourceFile
00267         }
00268 
00269         writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:function
